<div class="c230_128">
<div id="v230.128.1"><span class="H7892 s">A Song</span><span class="H4609 s"> of degrees</span><span class="H835 s">. Blessed</span><span class="H3373 s"> <i>is</i> every one that feareth</span><span class="H3068 s"> the LORD</span><span class="H1980 s">; that walketh</span><span class="H1870 s"> in his ways</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.128.2"><span class="H398 s">For thou shalt eat</span><span class="H3018 s"> the labour</span><span class="H3709 s"> of thine hands</span><span class="H835 s">: happy</span><span class="H2896 s"> <i>shalt</i> thou <i>be</i>, and <i>it shall be</i> well</span> with thee.</div>
<div id="v230.128.3"><span class="H802 s">Thy wife</span><span class="H6509 s"> <i>shall be</i> as a fruitful</span><span class="H1612 s"> vine</span><span class="H3411 s"> by the sides</span><span class="H1004 s"> of thine house</span><span class="H1121 s">: thy children</span><span class="H2132 s"> like olive</span><span class="H8363 s"> plants</span><span class="H5439 s"> round about</span><span class="H7979 s"> thy table</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.128.4"><span class="H1397 s">Behold, that thus shall the man</span><span class="H1288 s"> be blessed</span><span class="H3373 s"> that feareth</span><span class="H3068 s"> the LORD</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.128.5"><span class="H3068 s">The LORD</span><span class="H1288 s"> shall bless</span><span class="H6726 s"> thee out of Zion</span><span class="H7200 s">: and thou shalt see</span><span class="H2898 s"> the good</span><span class="H3389 s"> of Jerusalem</span><span class="H3117 s"> all the days</span><span class="H2416 s"> of thy life</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.128.6"><span class="H7200 s">Yea, thou shalt see</span><span class="H1121 s"> thy children's</span><span class="H1121 s"> children</span><span class="H7965 s">, <i>and</i> peace</span><span class="H3478 s"> upon Israel</span>.</div></div>
